         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Union"},{"id":"b","text":"Pivot"},{"id":"c","text":"Data Interpreter"},{"id":"d","text":"Custom Split"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states that 'Pivot: transform wide data to long (multiple columns to one column).' This is exactly the transformation described — collapsing multiple month columns into a single value column with a corresponding label column. Union stacks rows from tables with the same columns. Data Interpreter cleans Excel files. Custom Split parses text by delimiter.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/pivot.htm","label":"Tableau — Pivot Data from Columns to Rows"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
