  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau Desktop, which join type returns ALL rows from the left table and only the matching rows from the right table, filling non-matching rows on the right with null values?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Inner Join"},{"id":"b","text":"Left Join"},{"id":"c","text":"Right Join"},{"id":"d","text":"Full Outer Join"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material lists the four physical join types as 'Inner, Left, Right, Full Outer.' A Left Join preserves all rows from the left table and brings in matching rows from the right table; unmatched right-table rows produce nulls. An Inner Join returns only matching rows from both tables. A Right Join keeps all rows from the right table. A Full Outer Join keeps all rows from both tables.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/joining_tables.htm","label":"Tableau — Join Your Data"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
