         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Tableau Server"},{"id":"b","text":"Tableau Public"},{"id":"c","text":"Tableau Prep Builder"},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Reader"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly identifies 'Tableau Prep Builder: separate visual tool for advanced data prep (Input/Clean/Pivot/Join/Union/Aggregate/Script/Output steps).' Tableau Server is a platform for publishing and sharing workbooks. Tableau Public is a free platform for public visualizations. Tableau Reader is a free viewer for packaged workbooks — none of these provide the dedicated data preparation workflow that Prep Builder offers.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
