  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A user wants to see only the top 10 products by total sales. Which filter type is the most appropriate?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Dimension filter with a wildcard match"},{"id":"b","text":"Top N filter"},{"id":"c","text":"Date filter with a relative range"},{"id":"d","text":"Context filter"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The Top N filter is specifically designed to limit results to the top (or bottom) N members ranked by a measure such as total sales. A dimension filter restricts by category value, a date filter applies to date fields, and a context filter restricts the pool of data but does not rank. The source material lists 'Top N filter' under Filters.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/filters_top.htm","label":"Tableau Top N Filters"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
