  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$What is the primary difference between a Tableau Group and a Tableau Set?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Groups are numeric; Sets are string-based."},{"id":"b","text":"Groups combine members into static categories; Sets define dynamic IN/OUT membership based on conditions."},{"id":"c","text":"Groups are calculated fields; Sets are dimension filters."},{"id":"d","text":"Groups support Top N logic; Sets only support manual selection."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material describes Groups as 'static category combining' and Sets as 'dynamic with conditions or top N.' Groups merge dimension members into fixed, named buckets. Sets evaluate conditions at runtime (e.g., top N or a threshold condition) and assign each member an IN or OUT status, making them dynamic. Option D has the relationship backwards — Top N is a Set feature.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/groups_creating.htm","label":"Tableau Groups"},{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/sortgroup_sets_creating.htm","label":"Tableau Sets"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'TDS-C01-P1'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$What is the primary difference between a Tableau Group and a Tableau Set?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A Tableau Parameter differs from a filter because a parameter:$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Automatically applies to all worksheets in a workbook."},{"id":"b","text":"Allows users to pass a single dynamic value into calculations, filters, or reference lines."},{"id":"c","text":"Can only be used with date fields."},{"id":"d","text":"Creates a static list of values that cannot be changed at runtime."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material defines a Parameter as a 'user-editable single value' that can feed into calculated fields, filters, or reference lines, giving users control over a single input at runtime. Parameters are not restricted to dates (option C), do not automatically apply everywhere (option A), and are editable at runtime, making them dynamic rather than static (option D).$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
