         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Tableau Cloud supports dashboards while Tableau Server does not"},{"id":"b","text":"Tableau Cloud is a SaaS offering managed by Tableau, while Tableau Server is self-hosted by the organization"},{"id":"c","text":"Tableau Server is free and Tableau Cloud requires a paid license"},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Cloud can only publish data sources, while Tableau Server can publish full workbooks"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly distinguishes: 'Tableau Cloud (SaaS) vs Tableau Server (self-hosted).' Tableau Cloud is a fully managed cloud service operated by Tableau/Salesforce, while Tableau Server is installed and maintained on the organization's own infrastructure. The other options are fabricated distinctions not supported by the source material.$patch$, $patch$Sharing Insights$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/online/en-us/to_get_started.htm","label":"Tableau — Tableau Cloud vs Tableau Server"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
