INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A user has a table where each month's sales is stored in a separate column (Jan_Sales, Feb_Sales, Mar_Sales, etc.). They want to restructure this into two columns: one for the month name and one for the sales value. Which feature in the Tableau Data Source page accomplishes this?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Union"},{"id":"b","text":"Pivot"},{"id":"c","text":"Data Interpreter"},{"id":"d","text":"Split"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material describes Pivot as the feature that transforms 'wide data to long (multiple columns to one column).' Converting Jan_Sales, Feb_Sales, Mar_Sales into a Month column and a Sales column is exactly a wide-to-long transformation. Union stacks rows, not columns. Data Interpreter cleans Excel formatting. Split breaks a single text column by delimiter.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/pivot.htm","label":"Tableau Help – Pivot Data from Columns to Rows"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
