INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau Desktop, which join type returns ALL rows from the left table and only matching rows from the right table, filling in NULL for non-matching rows on the right?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Inner Join"},{"id":"b","text":"Right Join"},{"id":"c","text":"Full Outer Join"},{"id":"d","text":"Left Join"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["d"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material lists physical join types as 'Inner, Left, Right, Full Outer.' A Left Join keeps all rows from the left table and matches from the right, placing NULL where no match exists — exactly the behavior described. An Inner Join returns only matching rows. A Right Join keeps all rows from the right table. A Full Outer Join returns all rows from both tables.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
