         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Tableau Prep Builder"},{"id":"b","text":"Tableau Reader"},{"id":"c","text":"Tableau Bridge"},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Prep Conductor"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states: 'Tableau Bridge (keeps Cloud connected to on-prem data sources).' Tableau Prep Builder is a data preparation tool, Tableau Reader is a free viewer for packaged workbooks, and Tableau Prep Conductor is used for server-side flow scheduling — none of these address the on-premises connectivity requirement for Tableau Cloud.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/online/en-us/qs_bridge_launcher.htm","label":"About Tableau Bridge — Tableau Cloud Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
