         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Tableau Desktop"},{"id":"b","text":"Tableau Public"},{"id":"c","text":"Tableau Server"},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Prep Builder"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material describes Tableau Public as 'free, public dashboards' and notes that 'Public is free but workbooks save to public web.' This makes it the correct choice for sharing interactive content publicly at no cost to the author or viewer. Tableau Desktop is a paid authoring tool. Tableau Server requires organizational infrastructure and licensing. Tableau Prep Builder is a data preparation tool, not a sharing platform.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/public/desktop/en-us/public_overview.htm","label":"Tableau Public Overview — Tableau Public Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
