INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$On the Tableau Desktop Data Source page, an analyst drags a second table alongside the first table and a join dialog appears. Which join type returns ALL rows from the left table and only matching rows from the right table?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Inner Join"},{"id":"b","text":"Right Join"},{"id":"c","text":"Left Join"},{"id":"d","text":"Full Outer Join"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A Left Join returns all rows from the left (first) table and only the matching rows from the right table; non-matching rows from the right produce NULLs. The source material enumerates: 'Joins (physical): Inner, Left, Right, Full Outer.' An Inner Join returns only matching rows from both tables. A Right Join keeps all rows from the right table. A Full Outer Join returns all rows from both tables.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/joining_tables.htm","label":"Tableau – Join Your Data"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
