         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Union"},{"id":"b","text":"Data Interpreter"},{"id":"c","text":"Pivot"},{"id":"d","text":"Custom Split"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'Pivot: transform wide data to long (multiple columns to one column).' Selecting the twelve month columns and choosing Pivot restructures them into a single Month column and a corresponding Sales Amount column. Union stacks rows from multiple tables. Data Interpreter removes formatting noise from Excel. Custom Split parses values within a single text field.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/pivot.htm","label":"Tableau – Pivot Data from Columns to Rows"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
