  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which number function rounds a decimal value DOWN to the nearest integer (toward negative infinity)?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"ROUND"},{"id":"b","text":"ABS"},{"id":"c","text":"CEILING"},{"id":"d","text":"FLOOR"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["d"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$FLOOR(number) returns the largest integer less than or equal to the number — it always rounds toward negative infinity (down). CEILING rounds up to the nearest integer. ROUND rounds to the nearest integer (or specified decimal places). ABS returns the absolute value of a number. For example, FLOOR(4.9) returns 4 and FLOOR(-4.1) returns -5.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/functions_functions_number.htm","label":"Tableau Help — Number Functions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
