         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Reference Line"},{"id":"b","text":"Trend Line"},{"id":"c","text":"Cluster"},{"id":"d","text":"Forecast"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The Cluster feature in the Analytics pane applies a k-means clustering algorithm to group marks based on their proximity in the measure space. Each mark is assigned to one of k clusters, which Tableau then colors distinctly. Reference Lines add static or aggregate-based lines to the axis. Trend Lines fit mathematical models to the existing data distribution. Forecast projects values forward in time using exponential smoothing. Only Cluster performs unsupervised grouping of marks.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
