  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which file format is NOT listed as a supported file-based data source in Tableau Desktop?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"JSON"},{"id":"b","text":"PDF"},{"id":"c","text":"SPSS (.sav)"},{"id":"d","text":"Microsoft Access (.accdb)"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["d"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material, Tableau Desktop supports the following file-based sources: Excel (.xlsx), CSV, JSON, PDF, spatial files (shapefile, GeoJSON, KML), and statistical files (SAS, SPSS). Microsoft Access (.accdb) is not listed among the supported file-based sources in the source material. JSON, PDF, and SPSS are all explicitly mentioned. While Tableau does have an Access connector in practice, it is categorized differently and is not in the enumerated file-based list provided here.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/exampleconnections_overview.htm","label":"Tableau Help — Supported Connectors"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
