  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau Desktop, which of the following best describes a 'Union' on the Data Source page?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Combining two tables horizontally by matching rows on a common key field"},{"id":"b","text":"Stacking rows from multiple tables that share the same column structure"},{"id":"c","text":"Blending data from two separate data source connections using a linking field"},{"id":"d","text":"Creating a relationship between two logical tables in the data model"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A Union appends rows from two or more tables that share the same column structure, effectively stacking them vertically into a single table. This is different from a Join (horizontal combination on a key), a Blend (combining separate connections via a linking dimension), or a Relationship (logical layer connection). The source material states: 'Unions: combine tables with same columns; wildcard union (file pattern) or manual union.' Option A describes a Join. Option C describes Data Blending. Option D describes a Relationship.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/union.htm","label":"Tableau Help — Union Your Data"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
