  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau Desktop, a field displayed with a blue pill and labeled as a 'Dimension' typically represents which kind of data?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Quantitative data that is aggregated by default using SUM or AVG"},{"id":"b","text":"Qualitative, categorical data used to slice or partition the view"},{"id":"c","text":"Continuous data that always produces an axis when placed on a shelf"},{"id":"d","text":"A calculated field that references only measure fields"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Dimensions in Tableau are qualitative, categorical fields shown as blue pills. They are used to partition and categorize data in a view (e.g., Region, Category, Customer Name). Measures (green pills) are quantitative and aggregated by default. Continuous fields (green) produce an axis, while discrete fields (blue) produce headers. The source material states: 'Dimensions (qualitative, blue pill): discrete, typically categorical' and 'Measures (quantitative, green pill): aggregated by default (SUM/AVG/COUNT/etc).' Option C incorrectly conflates the continuous/discrete property with dimension/measure roles.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/datafields_typesandroles_dataroles.htm","label":"Tableau Help — Dimensions and Measures, Blue and Green"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
