         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Data Interpreter"},{"id":"b","text":"Pivot"},{"id":"c","text":"Custom Split"},{"id":"d","text":"Wildcard Union"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Custom Split (or Split) allows a user to parse a text field into separate parts using a specified delimiter — in this case, a comma — and then select which token(s) to keep. The source material states: 'Split / Custom Split: parse text columns by delimiter.' Data Interpreter is for cleaning Excel formatting issues. Pivot transforms column structure. Wildcard Union combines multiple files matching a filename pattern. Custom Split is the correct tool for extracting the city portion from a delimited address string.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/split.htm","label":"Tableau Help — Split a Field into Multiple Fields"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
