         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"COUNT([Product Name])"},{"id":"b","text":"LEN([Product Name])"},{"id":"c","text":"MID([Product Name])"},{"id":"d","text":"FIND([Product Name])"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$LEN is the string function that returns the number of characters in a string. COUNT is an aggregation function that counts the number of rows, not characters. MID extracts a substring by position, and FIND returns the position of a substring — neither measures string length. The source material lists LEN under 'String' calculated field functions.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
