         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The shipping date formatted as a day name"},{"id":"b","text":"The number of days between Order Date and Ship Date"},{"id":"c","text":"The order date truncated to the day level"},{"id":"d","text":"The day-of-year number for the Ship Date"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$DATEDIFF(date_part, start_date, end_date) returns the difference between two dates in the specified date_part unit. Using 'day' returns the integer number of days between Order Date and Ship Date. DATETRUNC truncates a date, and DATEPART extracts a component — those do not compute differences. The source material explicitly lists DATEDIFF under date functions.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
