         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Dimension filter"},{"id":"b","text":"Context filter"},{"id":"c","text":"Top N filter"},{"id":"d","text":"Relative date filter"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A Top N filter is specifically designed to limit a view to the top (or bottom) N members of a dimension ranked by a measure such as Sales. A Dimension filter excludes categorical values but does not automatically rank them. A Context filter establishes a dependent filter hierarchy but does not itself rank by measure. A Relative date filter operates only on date fields. The source material lists 'Top N filter' as one of the filter types.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/filtering.htm#create-top-n-filters","label":"Tableau — Filter Data from Your Views (Top N)"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
