  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau, a Context filter is best described as which of the following?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"A filter that applies only to measures, not dimensions"},{"id":"b","text":"An independent filter that is computed first and establishes a reduced data set for all other dependent filters"},{"id":"c","text":"A filter that sends selections from one sheet to another on a dashboard"},{"id":"d","text":"A filter that is applied only when the user interacts with a tooltip"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A Context filter is processed before all other filters in Tableau's order of operations, creating a temporary table of the filtered data against which subsequent filters (such as Top N) are evaluated. This allows Top N filters to operate only within the context. A filter that sends selections between sheets is a Filter Action, not a Context filter. The source material categorises Context filters as a distinct filter type.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/filtering_context.htm","label":"Tableau — Add Context Filters"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
