  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which LOD expression computes the average Sales per Customer, regardless of any dimensions currently in the view?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"{ INCLUDE [Customer] : AVG([Sales]) }"},{"id":"b","text":"{ EXCLUDE [Customer] : AVG([Sales]) }"},{"id":"c","text":"{ FIXED [Customer] : AVG([Sales]) }"},{"id":"d","text":"AVG([Sales])"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$FIXED LOD expressions compute the aggregation at the specified dimension level without being influenced by other dimensions in the view. { FIXED [Customer] : AVG([Sales]) } always calculates AVG(Sales) per Customer no matter what else is on the view. INCLUDE adds a dimension to the view level of detail; EXCLUDE removes one. A plain AVG([Sales]) simply aggregates at whatever level is in the view. The source material defines FIXED as 'compute at the dim level regardless of view'.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/calculations_calculatedfields_lod_overview.htm","label":"Tableau — Level of Detail Expressions"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
