  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$What is the key difference between a Group and a Set in Tableau?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Groups are dynamic and can update based on conditions; Sets are static."},{"id":"b","text":"Sets are dynamic and can be defined with conditions or Top N; Groups are static combinations of category members."},{"id":"c","text":"Groups work only with measure fields; Sets work only with dimension fields."},{"id":"d","text":"Sets can only contain two members; Groups can contain any number."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material, Groups are 'static category combining' (you manually select members to merge) while Sets are 'dynamic with conditions or top N', meaning they can automatically recalculate their membership based on defined rules. Both Groups and Sets are created from dimension fields, not measures. There is no two-member limit on Sets.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/sortgroup_sets_create.htm","label":"Tableau — Create Sets"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
