  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$You want to let report viewers change a threshold value between 1 and 100 at runtime without editing the workbook. Which Tableau feature should you use?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"A Context filter"},{"id":"b","text":"A Parameter"},{"id":"c","text":"A Set"},{"id":"d","text":"A Calculated Field with FIXED LOD"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Parameters are user-editable single-value controls that can be placed in a view and referenced in calculated fields, filters, or reference lines. They allow viewers to interactively change a value at runtime. A Context filter is not user-editable in this way. A Set defines in/out membership, not a free numeric threshold. A FIXED LOD is a calculation, not a user input control. The source material describes Parameters as 'user-editable single value'.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/parameters_create.htm","label":"Tableau — Create Parameters"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
