  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In the Analytics pane, which option allows you to add a k-means grouping to the marks in your view?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Trend Line"},{"id":"b","text":"Cluster"},{"id":"c","text":"Reference Distribution"},{"id":"d","text":"Forecasting"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The Cluster option in the Analytics pane applies k-means clustering to the marks in the current view, automatically assigning each mark to one of k groups based on similarity across the measures used. Trend Lines model relationships between variables but do not group marks. Reference Distribution highlights statistical spread. Forecasting projects future values. The source material states 'Cluster (k-means)' under the Analytics pane.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/clustering.htm","label":"Tableau — Find Clusters in Data"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
