  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A filter placed on the Filters shelf currently applies only to the current worksheet. You want the same filter to apply to all sheets that use the same data source. Which setting should you choose?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Apply to worksheets > Only This Worksheet"},{"id":"b","text":"Apply to worksheets > All Using This Data Source"},{"id":"c","text":"Add the filter to the Context"},{"id":"d","text":"Convert the filter to a Set"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Right-clicking a filter and choosing 'Apply to worksheets > All Using This Data Source' (equivalent to 'all using related data sources' for a single data source) makes the filter global across all sheets connected to that source in the workbook. 'Only This Worksheet' restricts it to the current sheet. Adding to Context changes filter order-of-operations, not scope. Converting to a Set creates a reusable set object, not a cross-sheet filter. The source material lists 'Apply to: only this worksheet, all using related data sources' as filter scope options.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/filtering_global.htm","label":"Tableau — Apply Filters to Multiple Worksheets"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'TDS-C01-P4'
