  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An author is building a dashboard and wants to group multiple sheets side by side so they resize together as a unit. Which dashboard container type should be used?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Floating container"},{"id":"b","text":"Horizontal container"},{"id":"c","text":"Tiled container"},{"id":"d","text":"Blank object"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states that dashboard containers include Horizontal, Vertical, Tiled, and Floating types, and that 'layout containers group objects.' A Horizontal container arranges child objects side by side and causes them to resize together. A Vertical container stacks objects top to bottom. Tiled refers to the overall tiled layout mode. A Blank object is a spacer, not a grouping container.$patch$, $patch$Sharing Insights$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/dashboards_organize_floatingandtiled.htm","label":"Tableau — Use Layout Containers to Organize Dashboard Content"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
