         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"MP4 (video file)"},{"id":"b","text":"DOCX (Word document)"},{"id":"c","text":"JSON (JavaScript Object Notation file)"},{"id":"d","text":"EXE (executable file)"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material, Tableau Desktop supports file-based connectors including JSON files, along with Excel (.xlsx), CSV, PDF, spatial files, and statistical files (SAS, SPSS). MP4, DOCX, and EXE are not supported file-based data sources in Tableau Desktop.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/connect_basic_connect.htm","label":"Tableau — Supported Connectors"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
