  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An analyst has a wide table where survey responses are spread across 12 separate columns (one per month). They want to restructure this into a single 'Month' column and a single 'Response' column. Which Tableau Data Source page feature accomplishes this?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Union"},{"id":"b","text":"Split"},{"id":"c","text":"Pivot"},{"id":"d","text":"Inner Join"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Pivot transforms wide-format data to long-format data by converting multiple columns into rows — exactly what is needed here to collapse 12 month columns into a single 'Month' column and a corresponding 'Response' value column. The source states: 'Pivot: transform wide data to long (multiple columns to one column).' Union appends rows; Split parses text by delimiter; an Inner Join merges tables by matching keys.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
