  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau Desktop, which of the following correctly describes the difference between a continuous field and a discrete field?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Continuous fields create headers; discrete fields create axes."},{"id":"b","text":"Continuous fields create axes; discrete fields create headers."},{"id":"c","text":"Both continuous and discrete fields always create axes."},{"id":"d","text":"Continuous fields are always dimensions; discrete fields are always measures."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states: 'Continuous fields create axes; discrete fields create headers.' Green (continuous) pills produce a quantitative axis along which values flow uninterrupted, while blue (discrete) pills produce distinct header labels for each value. Option A reverses the correct relationship. Option C is incorrect because discrete fields produce headers, not axes. Option D is wrong because any field — dimension or measure — can be made continuous or discrete in Tableau.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
         2, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/datafields_typesandroles_dataroles_continuous.htm","label":"Continuous and Discrete Fields – Tableau Desktop and Web Authoring Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
