  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau's order of operations, which filter type is evaluated BEFORE dimension filters but AFTER extract filters and data source filters?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Table calculation filters"},{"id":"b","text":"INCLUDE LOD filters"},{"id":"c","text":"Context filters"},{"id":"d","text":"Measure filters"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material, Tableau's order of operations is: 'Extract filters → Data source filters → Context filters → FIXED LODs → Dimension filters → INCLUDE/EXCLUDE LODs → Measure filters → Table calcs.' Context filters occupy the third position — after extract and data source filters, but before FIXED LOD expressions and dimension filters. INCLUDE/EXCLUDE LODs come after dimension filters; measure filters come even later; and table calculation filters are last in the sequence.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
