         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Tableau Cloud is self-hosted by the customer; Tableau Server is managed by Salesforce."},{"id":"b","text":"Tableau Cloud is a SaaS offering managed by Salesforce; Tableau Server is self-hosted by the customer."},{"id":"c","text":"Tableau Cloud supports only fixed-size dashboards; Tableau Server supports responsive dashboards."},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Cloud requires embedded credentials only; Tableau Server supports prompt-user credentials only."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states: 'Tableau Cloud (SaaS) vs Tableau Server (self-hosted).' Tableau Cloud is a fully managed, Software-as-a-Service platform operated by Salesforce, requiring no customer infrastructure. Tableau Server is installed and maintained on customer-owned or customer-managed infrastructure. Options C and D describe fictitious limitations not found in the source material.$patch$, $patch$Sharing Insights$patch$,
