         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The field is a dimension used for grouping data."},{"id":"b","text":"The field is continuous and will generate an axis when placed on a shelf."},{"id":"c","text":"The field is discrete and will generate column or row headers."},{"id":"d","text":"The field is a calculated field created by the author."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material: 'Continuous fields create axes; discrete fields create headers.' Continuous fields are shown in GREEN. When a continuous (green) field is placed on the Rows or Columns shelf, Tableau renders a continuous axis rather than discrete headers. Blue fields are discrete and produce headers. Color does not inherently indicate a dimension or a calculated field.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
