  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau's order of operations, which filter type is evaluated FIRST before all other filter types?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Context filters"},{"id":"b","text":"Data source filters"},{"id":"c","text":"Extract filters"},{"id":"d","text":"Dimension filters"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material lists the Tableau order of operations as: 'Extract filters → Data source filters → Context filters → FIXED LODs → Dimension filters → INCLUDE/EXCLUDE LODs → Measure filters → Table calcs.' Extract filters are applied at the point the extract is created from the data source and therefore execute before any other filter in the pipeline. Data source filters come second, followed by context filters, and so on.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
         1, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/order_of_operations.htm","label":"Tableau Order of Operations — Tableau Desktop Documentation"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
