  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$According to Tableau visual best practices, which of the following statements best describes the recommended use of color in a dashboard?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Use as many distinct colors as possible to make the dashboard visually engaging."},{"id":"b","text":"Use color sparingly so it draws attention only to what matters most."},{"id":"c","text":"Apply color only to measure fields; never color dimension headers."},{"id":"d","text":"Color should always match the corporate brand palette regardless of data meaning."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states under visual best practices: 'less is more; use color sparingly; consistent encoding.' Using color sparingly ensures it remains a meaningful pre-attentive attribute that directs the viewer's eye to the most important information. Overusing color (option A) defeats its purpose as a signal. Options C and D introduce restrictions not supported by the source material and contradict the principle of using color to highlight what matters.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
         1, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/visual_best_practices.htm","label":"Visual Best Practices — Tableau Desktop Documentation"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
