  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$In Tableau, which file extension represents a packaged workbook that bundles together the workbook XML and its associated data extract into a single file?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":".twb"},{"id":"b","text":".tds"},{"id":"c","text":".twbx"},{"id":"d","text":".hyper"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material, .twbx is the 'packaged workbook with data extract,' meaning it bundles the workbook XML along with any local data into one portable file. By contrast, .twb is just the workbook XML with no embedded data. .tds is a data source connection file (no workbook content), and .hyper is Tableau's in-memory extract format — not a workbook container.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
         1, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/environ_filesandfolders.htm","label":"Tableau File Types and Folders — Tableau Desktop and Web Authoring Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
