         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The field is a dimension used for categorical grouping."},{"id":"b","text":"The field is continuous and will produce an axis in the view."},{"id":"c","text":"The field is discrete and will produce column or row headers."},{"id":"d","text":"The field is a calculated field created by the author."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material: 'Continuous fields create axes; discrete fields create headers.' Green pills in Tableau represent continuous fields, which render as a continuous axis in the view. Blue pills represent discrete fields, which render as individual headers. The color green or blue does not indicate whether a field is calculated or a native dimension.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
         1, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/datafields_typesandroles_dataroles_continuous.htm","label":"Continuous and Discrete Fields — Tableau Desktop and Web Authoring Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
