         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Pivot"},{"id":"b","text":"Split"},{"id":"c","text":"Data Interpreter"},{"id":"d","text":"Union"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states that 'Data Interpreter: auto-clean Excel data (remove headers/footers/merged cells).' Pivot transforms wide data to long format. Split parses text columns by delimiter. Union combines tables with the same columns. None of these address merged cells or extra header rows.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
         1, $json$[{"url":"https://help.tableau.com/current/pro/desktop/en-us/data_interpreter.htm","label":"Clean Data from Excel with Data Interpreter — Tableau Help"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
