INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$On the Tableau Data Source page, what is the purpose of the Pivot feature?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"To combine two tables that share the same columns into a single table."},{"id":"b","text":"To transform wide data into long data by converting multiple columns into a single column."},{"id":"c","text":"To parse a text column into multiple columns using a delimiter."},{"id":"d","text":"To join two tables from different database connections."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material defines Pivot as: 'transform wide data to long (multiple columns to one column).' Option A describes a Union. Option C describes the Split feature. Option D describes a cross-database join. Pivot is specifically about reshaping column-oriented data into a row-oriented format.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
