  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which Tableau filter type is evaluated FIRST before all other filters and is used to restrict the data that subsequent filters act upon?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Dimension filter"},{"id":"b","text":"Measure filter"},{"id":"c","text":"Context filter"},{"id":"d","text":"Date filter"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Context filters are evaluated first in Tableau's filter order of operations. All other filters (dimension, measure, date, Top N, etc.) act only on the subset of data that the context filter has already isolated. Dimension filters simply restrict categorical values, measure filters restrict numeric aggregates, and date filters restrict by time — none of these establish an independent data context the way a context filter does.$patch$, $patch$Exploring and Analyzing Data$patch$,
