         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Inner Join"},{"id":"b","text":"Right Join"},{"id":"c","text":"Full Outer Join"},{"id":"d","text":"Left Join"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["d"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material lists join types as 'Inner, Left, Right, Full Outer.' A Left Join returns all rows from the left (primary) table and only matched rows from the right table — unmatched right rows are excluded. An Inner Join returns only matching rows. A Right Join returns all right rows and matched left rows. A Full Outer Join returns all rows from both tables regardless of match.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
