INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which Tableau product is specifically designed to keep Tableau Cloud connected to on-premises data sources that are behind a firewall?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Tableau Prep Builder"},{"id":"b","text":"Tableau Reader"},{"id":"c","text":"Tableau Bridge"},{"id":"d","text":"Tableau Prep Conductor"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material directly states: 'Tableau Bridge keeps Cloud connected to on-prem data sources.' It acts as a relay between Tableau Cloud (SaaS) and private or on-premises databases that are not publicly accessible. Tableau Prep Builder is for data preparation, Tableau Reader is a free viewer for .twbx files, and Tableau Prep Conductor handles server-side flow scheduling.$patch$, $patch$Understanding Tableau Concepts$patch$,
