  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which join type in Tableau returns ALL rows from the left table and only the matching rows from the right table, filling unmatched right-table fields with null?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Inner Join"},{"id":"b","text":"Right Join"},{"id":"c","text":"Left Join"},{"id":"d","text":"Full Outer Join"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material lists the physical join types as 'Inner, Left, Right, Full Outer.' A Left Join keeps all rows from the left (primary) table and matches what it can from the right table, leaving nulls where no match exists. An Inner Join keeps only matching rows; a Right Join keeps all right-table rows; a Full Outer Join keeps all rows from both tables.$patch$, $patch$Connecting to and Preparing Data$patch$,
